OVERVIEW
===========
Welcome to the Splunk "Kaggle App".
Using the 'kaggle' command, you can easily interact with the [Kaggle API](https://github.com/Kaggle/kaggle-api) and use most of the available endpoints - with almost the same syntax than with the Kaggle CLI
To interact with the API, you need to authenticate. Please refer to [this page](https://www.kaggle.com/docs/api#authentication) on how to get your personal API token.
Once you got your token, copy 'username' and 'key', add/save it on the "Setup Kaggle API Auth" page and you are good to go!

#Available Commands
###competitions
usage: kaggle competitions {list,files,download,leaderboard}
###datasets
usage: kaggle datasets {list,files,download,metadata}
###kernels
usage: kaggle kernels {list,pull,output,status}
